caption: Great service, really appreciate how careful they are being during the pandemic. The server recommended a wine and we each had a glass and really enjoyed it. We also got the cheese plate, which was great except for one cheese that we left behind because it tasted weird. Room 11 is always a tiny bit overpriced, but we’re still really sad it’s closing for the colder months. Hopefully it’s back in the spring!

Unusual requirement of wearing mask anytime we interact with the waiter even in the middle of our meal. Perhaps you might consider pop up trays that you set on the side and then customers pick up their own plates? One restaurant was handling things that way. No one else is requiring that we keep putting on our masks in between bites. I'd have also preferred my plates not picked up rather than to interrupt my conversation and meal, put on a mask so the waiter can take the plates.  I love room 11 and it's my first time back since the pandemic but not sure that I'd want to go back if it's such a hassle for questionable protection
really nice cute place ; sandwiches & coffee during the day ; bottled cocktails and beer available too. Lamby-Sammie was amazing !
Awesome!
Great burger & ambience

New York vibe with DC friendly service. Excellent and reasonably priced cocktails and a small but well-curated list of shared plates. Now I get why this place is so hyped as a first date spot (bonus for non-first dates is first-date people watching). Looking forward to making Room 11 part of our local rotation!
Parapluie Cocktail is a must
Love the laid-back vibes. The food and drink is always phenomenal. Beautiful, friendly energy among the staff and patrons.

Nice, cozy place to visit on a cold night. It's quite small, so I did have to wait a bit for a seat at the bar, but once seated everything was comfortable. The drinks that I had were quite well executed. This included one straight off the menu; a fino sherry drink with a cucumber syrup and lemon juice which was light and refreshing. Had a burger to eat, and was impressed by the price at $12. Similar burgers at similar places go for $15 or more. Finished up with a Smith and Cross daiquiri.

Love Room 11! Great staff, food, and cocktails. I eat here regularly and have never been disappointed. IMO, they have the best, most friendly staff in DC. I love coming here for that reason, but also their menu is so good -- many low carb options that are delicious. Highly recommend for happy hour, late night, anytime you need a good place to meet friends.
The drinks were delicious but expensive and the service was not very great.

What a lovely neighborhood bar - not only did my husband and I go for date night tonight, I went last Friday with friends too. Tonight I ordered the grilled cheese, OMG was it delicious. The bread was crunchy in all of the right places and the cheeses, shallots, etc were perfect. The spicy marinara sauce kicked the sandwich up to the next level. Wish I had another right now!

The service was great and the drinks were good. However, their dishes are something like a really small appetizer and extremely overpriced for the lack of uniqueness and size. So, to a person going to this place for the first time, you will be very hungry after eating at this place; and if you are ok with a “snack”, you will be paying a lot for it.

This is a neighborhood spot that cares about food and drink.  The cocktails are incredibly creative, and the dinner options are terrific (great risottos, grilled cheeses, burgers, and assorted vegetables such as brussel sprouts and asparagus).  The desserts are inventive.  Leave room for them.  The bartenders (Nate and Gavin, mostly, though there are others) take excellent care of you, and will make you a mocktail if you want it (invalidating the plangent nonsense about alcohol-centrism of a recent review).  If you want creative food and drink in a neighborhood setting with friendly staff, this place is for you. (If you want pink lemonade, head to Cheescake factory.)  My wife and I have been here monthly for the last six or seven years.  We hope that it will go on forever.
Outdoor seating, good food, great service.
We LOVED the food - especially the Salad - and the atmosphere!

The photo attached is not at all accurate - the offerings are beer. And more beer. And if you aren't sure - they also serve beer. I'm all for breweries and beer but the non alcoholic offerings were non existent and newsflash: not everyone who enjoys the company of their friends feels the need to consume alcohol alongside them.
Perfect date spot, especially when the weather is nice.

The bartender was awesome and knowledgeable. I was new in town and he was nice enough to explain the local drink and make one for me. Drinks were reasonably priced and a good charceuterie selection.  Would definitely visit again if I happen to be in town.
Super chill lighting and ambience. Great place for drinks and bar food
Really lovely,  great if you can sit out. Good food, good atmosphere.

A casual atmosphere, courteous and knowledgeable staff, and delicious food and beer. We went when it was packed and they were accommodating, if a bit delayed with service. Got charcuterie and a burger, which was one of the best burgers I've ever had, hands down.
Quite expensive and small portions
Our corner spot! Always good and relaxed!
Cozy and nice seating. They also have food.

What a gem! We wanted to find a fun bar that had great cocktails and wouldn't be overrun with frat boys. The service was impeccable and the cocktails were amazing. It's hard to beat finding a great cocktail bar that actually has a place to sit on a Saturday night!
Always great always wonderful
Cozy, no fuss. They certainly have a lot of drink choices.

I thought the food was good, but the menu is a bit too limited. And the menu online, unfortunately didn't match the menu in the actual restaurant. But the atmosphere was nice and relaxing. All in all, it's a pretty good place to enjoy a drink on a good weather day.

The servers here really know their stuff. They explain the menu very well and the food is great. Portions are not huge and prices can get a little high but the atmosphere is very nice and so is the presentation so it's a great date spot.
Great food, cocktails
Cost with excellent food and drinks.
Best craft cocktails around. Excellent food with small menu.

Room 11 is my neighborhood fancy cocktail bar and I couldn't be happier with it. They have a fantastic rotating list of cocktails. When it's nice out, sitting on the patio and enjoying a cocktail is one of my favorite things to do in Columbia Heights.  The food is pricey, but very good if you're in the mood for dinner.
Cozy bar, with small room that you cam rent for special occasions

Excellent cocktails and a fantastic whiskey list. I cannot overstate how good the cocktails are. Novel, complex, and nowhere near sweet (unless that's what you want.) Great bartenders, too. The space is a bit cramped, but don't let that turn you off, there's outdoor seating when the weather cooperates.
Our server was amazing. I always get the Quest que C'est.
The grilled cheese is it!
I am impressed
I've always had a lovely time with friends yummy meat and cheese boards and good wine to go with it
Cool
Good place to hang out with friends, they also have outdoor seating in summer. My mojito was alright, but the staff is friendly and accommodating. It was great fun. Try the grilled cheese sandwich!
Amazing, amazing food. Shared the risotto, grilled cheese and yogurt gazpacho with a friend. Ate every bite & couldn't stop raving over how good it was!
Very solid place. Good drinks, lovely service, good food. I had my first date with my husband here, so the ambience musta been good. Check it out you'll like it.
Love you
Good place,  not amazing.

Been here many times, never disappointed (well, except when they are so busy I couldn't even get a drink!) Great food from brunch to dinner/dessert... Cocktails are seasonal and delicious. It's a small space, so take that into consideration when heading there. Thankfully they have a good sized outdoor patio open in good weather (great for people watching) which doubles their capacity. Highly recommend.
Cliché hipster place. Great cocktails and pricey glasses of wine.
Great cocktails.
Chill place and nice scotch selection.
Great cocktails.
Great drinks, cozy atmosphere, not the most extensive menu, but what they DO have is delicious.

This is a neighborhood gem, almost next to my house. Great cocktails and wine, spacious patio. Food selection is improving lately. Couple years ago, they did an unforgivable move and shut down their day time cafe. One star is missing because, at times, when sitting at the bar, you may feel that you are crashing the bar attenders' house party.

Excellent wine and cocktail menu. A little on the pricey side but it's comparable to the prices in the Columbia Heights area. It's smaller than most bars but I think that only adds to the appeal of this place. Very inventive cocktails too. I look forward to going back and trying some more of them as well as getting some food.
Best drinks in D.C., and I'm happy to report that's not changed since this place first opened.
Definitely enjoyed dinner here. Charcuterie was great. Roasted cauliflower was underwhelming. Salt cod croquettes were amazing. Server was helpful. Worth a visit!
Great bartender. Awesome food!
Amazing cocktails and host/bartender!
Mixed feelings
We went for cocktails. Drinks and service were excellent. I recommend the buttery rum.

Bit of a hidden gem on 11th street. Cozy place with friendly staff.  Great place to grab a drink and an appetizer. Great selection of mix drinks and wine. Bourbon/whiskey/rye drinkers - you will not be disappointed in the selection.  The dinner menu looked limited but good. Will have to come back some time.
The skate fish was delicious and the bartenders are really knowledgeable here.
GREAT LOCAL BAR and the food is pretty good.

A random find in Columbia Heights. It manages to be both hole-in-the-wall bar and clean. The brunch menu is simple but delicious and I have never waited long.  The mimosas were a little heavy on the orange juice, so it's not the place to be a "brunch skunk" on the weekend.
Quaint bar and restaurant. Brunch was great!

Always wonderful neighborhood restaraunt.  Some till he most creative and friendly  bartenders with an unparalleled collection of premium liquors.  Evovling seasonal menu with great standards. You can get lost in the wonderful ambiance and feel like you are in any of the great world cities!
Gorgeous cocktail bar in great location. Highly recommended.
Though it's a cocktail place, I get a warm, non pretentious neighborhood bar feeling when I'm here.
loved it.  until we saw a rat scurry across the floor.  probably hard to prevent late at night with the doors open, but still unnerving.

The food is excellent and creative, and the cocktails are better on both fronts. The pour really original drinks here, with unexpected and delicious flavor profiles. Especially try the Rite of Spring!
A perfect, quiet neighborhood spot for great cocktails. The patio is great on nice nights!
Really cool bar. A little expensive for a small neighborhood joint.
Got the pork belly hash, cucumber gazpacho and hopping John's all of which were delightful. Damn good bloody marys as well. Lots of outdoor seating.
Good if sitting outdoors, can getty a little noisy but a fun comfy place
5 stars for service, 3 for food. The food was very solid, but not very interesting. Brunch is better than dinner, but definitely a solid neighborhood option.
Food is mediocre and I feel people only go here because the wait is so long at the places nearby
Great food and cocktails
Excellent food quality and attentive service.
Big favorite here, wish it could be bigger, but would loose its cozy charm I suppose.
Great food, w/ awesome cocktails, beer, and wine.

I ordered the pork belly and it was fantastic. Wonderfully cooked and crisp. All the food looks amazing and everyone in my party loved what they had. We sat outside because it was warm enough and it was beautiful. Overall, a great place to eat and a wonderful ambiance.

Had brunch on a Sunday morning and it was so so so wonderful. We both had eggs, cheese grits, and a jalapeno biscuit -- all so good. The ambiance of the restaurant was great, and it felt tucked away from the crazy bustle of the rest of post-inauguration DC/world.

Awesome food and staff true cocktail virtuosos. If you want to drink but don't know what, the staff is delightfully prejudiced toward bourbon. Before Room 11, I'd had plenty of Manhattans ... drinkable enough, but hardly a drink I'd call thoughtful.  Room 11 changed all that -- how i ordered and what I expected from a Manhattan, given that we're on the east coast, probably makes me a better person.

This was my first time - the food was good but the portions are on the smaller side. Our waitress was phenomenal - she remembered all of our special requests, allergies and dietary restrictions with grace and kindness!
Great cocktails and food
Fantastic drinks in the $12-14 range.

The bar here has just about anything that you may want and a hipsters paradise. While I was deciding on a real drink, I decided to go with a hot toddy and it was delicious. I asked the bartender if he could make me his preffered old fashioned. He whipped up a burnt sugar old fashioned with I believe west indies bitter and it was fantastic. The wine list was decent as well. Olives tasted quite fresh.
(Translated by Google) It is accessible and convenient  (Original) Es accesible y conveniente
They are transitioning, so they don't have coffee or tea in the evenings
Food is just as good as the amazing cocktails! If you're considering this place, it will not disappoint. Just get there early, the space is small and it's very popular so it can fill up fast!

Wonderful brunch spot for simple but delicious fare -- and the best Bloody Mary in town.  When in season the patio is great.  Also went for cocktails and dessert.  Tasty food and attentive service. Drinks are creative and clearly well-thought out, with knowledgeable bar staff. My first cocktail was a little overly-complicated-yet-simple-in-taste, but my second was great.  Also an impressive whiskey collection.  Great neighborhood spot!
Excellent food, atmosphere, service, and fellow patrons!

The best sangria, a great scotch and whisky selection. Great wines of course. Excellent menu of small plates and "new American" entrées. A pop up kitchen inside sells the best granola in the city (Paisley Fig).
They have delicious cocktails and the food is yummy too!

A highly-recommended Columbia Heights wine bar located within the 11th Street NW corridor of the city.  Among many pleasing attributes, Bar 11 is a "small but enormous in spirit" gathering place that specializes in improvisational cuisine and cocktails.   Upon your request, it's impressive staff will create a pleasing cocktail or serve a mouth-watering dish tailored to your specifications.

So chic that Wifi is not a viable offering, nor should it be with the popularity of the location. Astounding grilled cheese sandwiches and one of the more charming ambiances on 11th street. Great for dates, even better for getting your coworkers to actually show up outside of work.
Intimate setting with an extensive spirits selection
My favorite bar in DC: chill, cozy atmosphere, perfect lighting, top-notch staff, superb drinks, creative food.

Sadly, no happy hours at this place -- which made this visit a little pricier than most. The waiting staff knows their stuff in terms of alcohols and liqueurs, and also checked up on us plenty of times to see if we wanted more drinks or food. The food and drinks were pretty unique and delicious.

(Translated by Google) I was having dinner with my friend last week at this place and it is quite nice. What we liked the most, without a doubt, was the terrace. There is a quiet atmosphere, ages 22 to 38 and it is beautiful. The food was good, we ordered a risotto and it was very tasty, something lacking, but good. The negative point goes to the world of beers. They have no draft beer. Big bug. There was only glass beer and the cheapest one I think was worth 8 dollars. The waiters were all very nice and attentive.  (Original) Estuve la semana pasada cenando con mi amiga en este lugar y es bastante agradable. Lo que mas nos gustó, sin lugar a dudas, fue la terraza. Hay un ambiente tranquilo, con edades desde los 22 hasta los 38 y es bonita. La comida estaba buena, pedimos un risotto y estuvo muy rico, algo carete, pero bueno. El punto negativo va para el mundo de las cervezas. No tienen cerveza de barril. Gran fallo. Solo había cerveza de vidrio y la más barata creo recordar que valía 8 dólares. Los camareros fueron todos muy agradables y atentos.
Great cocktails, good large patio for the nice weather.
The breakfast biscuits are amazing and this place has some of my favorite scones! Also fast and friendly service.
Lovely cocktails and outdoor space
I LOVE this restaurant... the food is really delicious and I have never had a bad meal.  The staff is as great as the food and you cannot wait to return!
Good food and atmosphere, hit or miss service
Super coze local bar. Be sure to sit outside and try one of house cocktails!
Great staff, great food, great drinks, great atmosphere!

Food is excellent and cocktails are good. A little on the pricey side. Pruschitta was excellent and the boast a great cheese plate. Go when the weather is nice and you have a babysitter and you won't regret it. Not sure if I would bring my toddler but that's just my reading of the environment.
Excellent coffee. A tad small, but cute
The food here was superb.. Along with the atmosphere it was interesting, bold and extremely welcoming... I am sold, and I will definitely be back every time I visit the DC area...

The best drinks I've had in DC are here. The staff behind the bar are real, authentic and love what they do. They have unique, hard-to-find spirits and bitters and they know how to use them better than most places I've been. Sit at the bar and watch them work their magic.
Great cocktails and knowledgeable bartenders made this a great place to grab a drink while waiting for a table at a nearby restaurant.
Coffee burger delicious. Our server was super patient and accommodating and funny. Great place!

One of the best places in Columbia Heights and DC overall. Their staff is great, the cocktails are fantastic and the food is delicious. I've been there several times and it's always a positive experience. I really like their cocktail selection and how frequently they change. While the food menu is more or less the same, they have a wide selection and the food is ways consistently good. The Pork Belly for appetizer is amazing, their grilled cheese sandwich for a nice bite, a burger if you're slightly hungrier, and their short ribs if you really want to try something that will leave you wanting more -- the flavors are just awesome. Highly recommend.

Room 11 has a good selection of craft beers from all over the place. Their food menu is also good. I had a terrible specialty cocktail about a month ago, recommended by the server, and I now don't want to return. That it's also a coffee shop by day, though, might warrant another shot.

Really lovely little place on 11th St NW, with a seasonal menu and competent staff.  It doesn't take reservations so it can be a bit difficult to get in sometimes, but it's worth the wait.  One could easily fill up on the creative appetizer menu and drinks, but hopefully there's room for the entrees, which are genuinely creative and interesting.  In the non-winter months, there is a great patio, with a fire pit for cooler evenings.
Coffee in the morning, cocktails at night, all in a super cute space with a great patio and good vibes.

A buddy and I met for breakfast on a Saturday morning in the summer and he said the best breakfast in DC was Room 11 in Columbia Heights. Since he has good taste in food, I did not dispute him and I am glad I didn't. I loved Room 11. The pastries are supposed to be amazing (and they looked it), but I got their feta and zucchini quiche (It comes with the best side salad I've had in my life-mixed greens, roasted pine nuts, parmesan cheese, and a lemon vinaigrette dressing). My buddy got their gronala and it's the best I've had.  We sat outside which was perfect for a DC summer morning. Go here for sure!  (I took off one star only because they forgot my order due to the long line, but they made it up to me, so I still love this place).
Great brunch.
Great Burger, so innovative with the coffee accent. Cooked perfectly to order! I would definitely come back on my next DC visit. Small seating area, but this is what gives Room 11 its character!

Room 11 is an excellent local restaurant/bar/coffee house all in one. The patio is great to enjoy one of their delicious cocktails or a cold beer--they have a great selection. Not every dish is a homerun, but most everything we've ordered has been delicious and the service has been great.
Good beer, good food. Staff is really nice. To be honest, I've been there only once as a tourist and I do not rate 5 stars easily but I do recommend this place!
Very good food, friendly baristas and draft coffee!

Very good and cool place! I was in DC for the weekend and as the hostel I stayed at didn't offer breakfast I stopped by Room 11 to grab something to eat in the morning. They have great cappuccino and delicious pastries and also brunch options. Service was very good as well. If you are around Columbia Height you should definitely visit it!

Room 11 is truly a neighborhood gem! It's quaint and cozy and had some really great, unique cocktails. Although they have a small menu, their food is pretty delicious as well. The olives are a must. Room 11 is also a great spot to pick up some coffee and baked good. The cardamom apricot scone is a real winner.
username: M U K T I . D E S A I

caption: Whether it's 6:00 AM and you are needing a strong coffee with a biscuit, grabbing a fancy drink after work, or trying to impress that special someone Room 11 fits the need. If you can stand a crowd then it's a perfect place to grab a drink and loosen up before you start working those muscles on the dance floor of Wonderland Ballroom next door. All in all they make wonderful and creative food that is expensive, but not break the bank expensive.  My only complaint is that it is often too packed (because they have great food and the neighborhood knows), and the morning rush can have you waiting a bit too long for a coffee.
perfect from the word go. the sweet potato bisque was exquisite, the butternut squash risotto was superb, and the atmosphere was comfortable and inviting!

What an excellent grilled cheese that keeps getting better with each bite!! The craft cocktails are solid, the decor is euro cafe, and the prices are reasonable. Definitely recommend checking out this neighborhood spot in Columbia Heights.

After being on call and eating nothing but hospital food for 3 days, my husband came by near my work for a quick dinner date. I chose Room 11 after walking by a few weeks prior and remembered shrimp and grits (my new obsession) on the menu.  I was the first to arrive and this place was packed with patrons standing all around. Luckily, I managed to snatch the last table available inside. Perhaps because it was Friday dinner hours, it became quite obvious that this place was understaffed. After being seated, it took quite some time for anyone to come by to take our orders. We made several attempts to gesture that we were ready. Even with our waitress' acknowledgment, we waited another 10 mins.  Their food menu is limited compared to their drinks. Being on call meant I had only the food to focus on. My husband went with their pork chop while I went their shrimp and grits. The wait wasn't as bad for the foods to arrive.  Both the entree sizes were right on. It was love at first sight where I couldn't wait to devour my beautiful bowl of cheesy grits with 6 jumbo shrimp swimming on top of aromatic gravy. And it tasted even more amazing! Hands down the best shrimp and grits Ive ever had! My husband took a bite and was so impressed (he never order shrimp and grits because he's not a fan or shrimp or grits - but this time, he wouldn't stop eating off my plate which I was a bit annoyed about - hey hey I'm the one who's been on call!). My husband didn't love the pork chop however since he thought it was a bit overcooked and had too much of a lemony taste. The Brussels sprouts were also undercooked and almost inedible.  Overall -  5 stars for my lovely dish, 2 stars for everything else. With the most amazing shrimp and grits, if the wait and service weren't taking forever, I would return for it post call every time.
Amazing and creative cocktails. Well worth the wait if there on a Saturday

I'll give Room 11 this: their pastry selections for breakfast are really good. They have a variety of scones and muffins that are very delicious and made in house. That's where my positivity about this place ends: Room 11 has to have the rudest, most obnoxious staff I think I've ever encountered. They treat you like you don't exist -- whether its long waits for food, ignoring you when you ask questions, or giving you the stink-eye when you ask for milk with your coffee. I don't think my wife and I have ever been treated as though we were...you know...paying customers. One time I ordered a glass of cab off the menu, and since it tasted unlike a california Cab (think it was from Oregon or something like that) I asked something innocuous like "Excuse me, what makes this cab taste so different from a california one?" The waitress literally rolled her eyes at me and walked away. Their entrees are overpriced and so are their wines. Do yourself a favor and stick to getting something to go from the brunch menu. Preferably in the morning when the staff isn't so hostile.

This bar has a lower East side nyc feeling which makes it one of my favorite drinking locations in the city.   The grilled cheese is excellent... And the bar tenders actually take the time to properly mix your cocktails.
Best cocktails I've ever had, wish they had a happy hour though.
an adorable nook to have a nightcap in
Love the beer and wine menu here.  Every time I've gone here I sat outside, but the patio is great.  Very nice food as well.
Love this little wine bar in columbia heights. Great selection of wines and cocktails.  Food is really good for dinner as well. Its become a place I frequent often in the neighborhood.
